ATTRIBUTION
This project draws on the following sources:

- MIT AI Risk Repository (CC BY 4.0)
  Slattery et al., 2024. airisk.mit.edu
  
- NIST AI Risk Management Framework 1.0 and AI 600-1
  National Institute of Standards and Technology (public domain)
  nist.gov/artificial-intelligence

- OWASP LLM Top 10 (CC BY-SA 4.0)
  owasp.org/www-project-top-10-for-large-language-model-applications

- EU AI Act (Regulation 2024/1689)
  European Parliament and Council (public domain)

- MITRE ATLAS (CC BY 4.0)
  atlas.mitre.org

Incident examples are drawn from publicly documented real-world events
and are cited with approximate dates. Scenario characters and organisations
are entirely fictional. Any resemblance to real persons or companies
is coincidental.

DISCLAIMER
This material is provided for educational purposes only. It does not
constitute legal, compliance, or professional advice. Risk ratings and
controls described are illustrative starting points, not prescribed
requirements. Organisations should conduct their own risk assessments
appropriate to their specific context and applicable regulations.
